This paper is primarily focused on wireless networks and their optimization using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes the use of neural networks for prediction, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Federated Learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the optimization of wireless networks, which can be considered as a control systems problem, falling under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the communication overhead for model transmission, which is a topic related to information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
